4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, child care facilities are
6 not required to have anaphylaxis training and response
7 procedures in place.
8 This bill would require the Department of Human
9 Resources to create an anaphylactic response policy.
10 This bill would require all licensed day care
11 centers, which are facilities that care for more than
12 12 children, to adopt and implement the anaphylactic
13 response policy.
14 This bill would also require all licensed day
15 care center employees to complete an approved
16 anaphylaxis training program.
17
18
19 A BILL
20 TO BE ENTITLED
21 AN ACT
22
23 Relating to day care centers; to require the Department
24 of Human Resources to create an anaphylactic response policy;
25 to require all licensed day care centers to adopt and
26 implement the anaphylactic response policy; and to require all
27 licensed day care center employees to complete an approved
28 anaphylaxis training program.
